I ran the sfv file for each folder: check.
I copied the last .0xx file for each folder and renamed ithe copy .r00.
This I then was able to extract with either winrar or Powerdesk each folder came up with file with no extension, but tacking on a .iso extension to that file gave me one  I could run or burn to disc with Alcohol 120%.

Annoying and sorta like playing with Russian dolls... but it worked.

I hope this is helpful.

The first disc has a keygen, the second a manual, and the last has a bunch of tutorials.
